content: Got some feedback on my AI ethics paper. Need to refine the section on AI autonomy. Emily and I are heading to the High Line for some photography inspiration.
Xander's AI now considers environmental impact in its trading decisions. Emily and I had a blast at the High Line, captured some great shots for our blog.
Just finished a draft of my talk for the DeFi conference. Emily's helping me practice. Xander's AI ethics are shaping up, feels like we're on the right track.
Xander's now suggesting alternative trading options when ethical conflicts arise. Emily and I are planning our next urban exploration. Also, got an email about a potential book deal!
Had an interesting chat with my mentor about AI's role in personal growth. Xander's learning to be more empathetic, and Emily and I are exploring an old factory this weekend.
Xander's AI is now more resource-efficient. Emily and I had an incredible time exploring that old factory, found some amazing graffiti. Got some ideas for our next blog post.
Just got some positive feedback on Xander's latest ethical trading sim. Emily's vegan pop-up is becoming popular. We're thinking about expanding it to other neighborhoods.
Spent the last few days refining Xander's AI for the conference demo. Emily and I are setting up a rooftop garden for our building. It's all about growth, both for us and Xander.

Xander's AI demo for the conference is ready. Emily and I have our rooftop garden underway, and we're planning to make it a community space. Feeling like we're making a difference, one small step at a time.
